{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2013}} {{Infobox person | name = Mary Lambert | image = | caption = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1951|10|13}} | birth_place = [[Helena, Arkansas]], U.S. | spouse = Jerome Gary<ref name=sister/> | relatives = [[Blanche Lincoln]] <small>(sister)</small> | occupation = [[Film director]] }} '''Mary Lambert''' (born October 13, 1951) is an American [[film director|director]]. She has directed music videos, television episodes and feature films, mainly in the horror genre.
==Life and career== Lambert was born in [[Helena, Arkansas]], the daughter of Martha Kelly and Jordan Bennett Lambert III, a rice and cotton farmer.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.govnotes.com/Directories/_Arkansas_Congressional_Directory.htm |title=Arkansas Congressional Directory |publisher=Govnotes.com |date= |accessdate=February 5, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120306192109/http://www.govnotes.com/Directories/_Arkansas_Congressional_Directory.htm |archivedate=March 6, 2012 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Her younger sister is former [[United States Senate|U.S. Senator]] [[Blanche Lincoln]] of [[Arkansas]].<ref name=sister>{{cite web|url=http://www.pressregister.com/articles/2008/06/25/news/doc486282de43b61264973227.txt|title=Sundance features Clarksdale visit|first=Andy|last=Ross}}</ref> Lambert graduated from the [[Rhode Island School of Design]] with a [[Bachelor of Fine Arts|B.F.A.]]
Lambert directed [[Chris Isaak]]'s first music video "Dancin'" and [[Janet Jackson]]'s "[[Nasty (song)|Nasty]]" and "[[Control (Janet Jackson song)|Control]]" music videos. She also directed videos for [[Annie Lennox]], [[Mick Jagger]], [[The Go-Go's]], [[Whitney Houston]], [[Alison Krauss]], [[Live (band)|Live]], [[Mötley Crüe]], [[Queensrÿche]], [[Sting (musician)|Sting]], [[Debbie Harry]], [[Tom Tom Club]] and others. She directed many of [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]]'s early videos including "[[Borderline (Madonna song)|Borderline]]", "[[Like a Virgin (song)|Like a Virgin]]", "[[Material Girl]]", "[[La Isla Bonita]]", and "[[Like a Prayer (song)|Like a Prayer]]".
In 1987 she released her debut feature, the stylish and controversial ''[[Siesta (film)|Siesta]]'', starring [[Ellen Barkin]] and [[Jodie Foster]]. It was nominated for the IFP Spirit Award for best first feature. She is known to horror fans for directing the 1989 adaptation of [[Stephen King]]'s novel ''[[Pet Sematary (1989 film)|Pet Sematary]]'' and its sequel, ''[[Pet Sematary Two]]''.<ref>[http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/89233/women-in-horror-month-spotlight-on-some-recent-female-directed-horror-films/ Mary Lambert directed the film’s sequel, Pet Sematary 2, followed by Urban Legends: Bloody Mary.]</ref> More recently, Lambert directed 2005's ''[[Urban Legends: Bloody Mary]]'' and the 2011 [[Syfy]] horror film ''[[Mega Python vs. Gatoroid]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/38523/mega-python-vs-gatoroid-adds-a-monkee|title=Mega Python vs. Gatoroid Adds a Monkee}}</ref>
She directed the 1993 [[Digital Pictures]] [[Full motion video|FMV]] video game ''[[Double Switch (video game)|Double Switch]]''.
